nl_problem:
# Task: valid_parentheses_complex
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: isValid(self, arg1)

Given a string containing just the characters '(', ')', '{', '}', '[' and ']', determine if the input string is valid.
An input string is valid if:
1. Open brackets must be closed by the same type of brackets.
2. Open brackets must be closed in the correct order.
3. Every close bracket has a corresponding open bracket of the same type.
Include support for nested and complex structures.

Constraints:
- 1 <= s.length <= 10^4
- s consists of parentheses only '()[]{}'.
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "isValid")
  (signature ( (s string) ) boolean)
  (constraints
    (constraint "The length of the input string s is between 1 and 10^4.")
    (constraint "The input string s consists only of parentheses '()[]{}'.")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Determine if the input string containing just the characters '(', ')', '{', '}', '[' and ']' is valid.")
    (rule "Open brackets must be closed by the same type of brackets.")
    (rule "Open brackets must be closed in the correct order.")
    (rule "Every close bracket has a corresponding open bracket of the same type.")
    (return "Return true if the string is valid, otherwise return false. Edge cases include empty strings and strings with only one character.")
  )
)
